gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Nuggets 117, Kings 96
gameRecap.excerpt: The Nuggets defeated the Kings 117-96. Jamal Murray led five Nuggets in double-figures as he had his sixth 30-point game of the year with 32 points on 13-15 FG, along with six assists and three rebounds as Nikola Jokic totaled his fourth straight triple-double and 19th of the year with 14 points, 14 rebounds, and 11 assists. Keegan Murray led Sacramento with 21 points while Domantas Sabonis recorded his 41st straight double-double and 54th of the year with 13 points, 10 rebounds, and seven assists. The Nuggets have now won four in a row as they improve to 40-19 while the Kings move to 33-25.
